Step 1. Calculate Debt to Equity Ratio  
• Total Liabilities = Total Assets – Total Owner's Equity  
  = 39,772,748.32 – 31,744,117.89  
  = 8,028,630.43  
• Debt to Equity Ratio = Total Liabilities / Total Owner's Equity  
  = 8,028,630.43 / 31,744,117.89  
  ≈ 0.253 (rounded to two decimal places, this is 0.25)

Step 2. Calculate Net Profit Margin  
• Net Profit = 3,744,117.89  
• Total Revenue = 28,572,608.70  
• Net Profit Margin = (Net Profit / Total Revenue) × 100%  
  = (3,744,117.89 / 28,572,608.70) × 100%  
  ≈ 13.11%

Step 3. Calculate Return on Assets (ROA)  
• Total Assets = 39,772,748.32  
• ROA = (Net Profit / Total Assets) × 100%  
  = (3,744,117.89 / 39,772,748.32) × 100%  
  ≈ 9.42%

Step 4. Calculate Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio  
• Accounts Receivable (beginning) = 0.00 (from 2023-12-31)  
• Accounts Receivable (ending) = 14,921,566.06 (from 2024-02-05)  
• Average Accounts Receivable = (0 + 14,921,566.06) / 2  
  = 7,460,783.03  
• Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio = Total Revenue / Average Accounts Receivable  
  = 28,572,608.70 / 7,460,783.03  
  ≈ 3.83

Thus, the answer in the required format is:

{"solution": {"Debt to Equity Ratio": "0.25", "Net Profit Margin": "13.11%", "Return on Assets (ROA)": "9.42%", "Accounts Receivable Turnover Ratio": "3.83"}}
